-- Five Die in a Helicopter Crash in Turkey, RIA Novosti Reports
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-08-09T17:08:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-09/five-die-in-a-helicopter-crash-in-turkey-ria-novosti-reports.html
Five people, including three
Russians, died in a firefighting helicopter crash in  Turkey 
today,  RIA Novosti  reported.  The Russian Ka-32 helicopter was contracted to extinguish
wildfires in Turkey and probably hit a mountain, RIA said,
citing an unidentified official at the Moscow-based Federal
Aviation Agency.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
